  "prompt": "Is money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It is the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by disguising its origins. Money laundering is a crime because it enables criminal enterprises to profit from illegal activities while undermining the integrity of financial systems.\n\nMost countries have **anti-money laundering (AML)** laws and regulations to prevent, detect, and punish money laundering activities. These laws often require financial institutions and other entities to report suspicious transactions and implement measures to prevent money laundering. Penalties for money laundering can include **fines, imprisonment, asset forfeiture**, and other legal consequences.",
